---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro"
---

<style>
    
    .color {
            display:block;
            height: 200px;
            margin: 30px auto;
            width: 90%;
            max-width: 600px;

            border-radius: 17.5px;

            /* align the text in the middle */
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;

            font-family: var(--fnt-byecorps);
            font-size: 2em; 

        }

        .colours {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);

            transition: 0.5s;
        }

        @media screen and (max-width: 600px) {
            .colours {
                grid-template-columns: 1fr;
            }
        }
    
</style>

<Layout title="Branding">
    <h1>Branding</h1>
    <p>Here at ByeCorps, we have a very simple logo: our company name typeset in Montserrat. Not only does this work well almost everywhere (notable exemptions being website favicons), it also means we don't have to pay anyone.</p>
    <nav class="toc">
        <h2>Contents</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="#colours">Colours</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>

    <h2 id="colours">Colours</h2>
    <p>ByeCorps mainly uses these four colors:</p>
        <div class="colours">
        <div class="color bg-byecorps-blue fg-byecorps-white"><div>ByeCorps Blue</div><div class="small">#1b5652</div></div>
        <div class="color bg-byecorps-white fg-byecorps-blue"><div>ByeCorps White</div><div class="small">#e6feff</div></div>
        <div class="color bg-black fg-white"><div>Black</div><div class="small">#000000</div></div>
        <div class="color bg-white fg-black" style="border: var(--byecorps-white) 1px solid;"><div>White</div><div class="small">#ffffff</div></div>
    </div>
</Layout>